"'Never.'

"'Why, I wonder at that, for you are eligible yourself for one of the vacancies.'

"'And what are they worth?' I asked.

"'Oh, merely a couple of hundred a year, but the work is slight, and it need not interfere very much
with one's other occupations.'

"Well, you can easily think that that made me prick up my ears, for the business has not been over-
good for some years, and an extra couple of hundred would have been very handy.